\begin_layout Theorem
For any fixed positive values of 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{\pm},\rho_{\pm}$
\end_inset

, if 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{-}-u_{+}>F(0;p_{\pm},\rho_{\pm})$
\end_inset

 or equivalently
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u_{-}+\frac{2a_{-}}{\gamma-1}>u_{+}-\frac{2a_{+}}{\gamma-1}
\]

\end_inset

then the following equation for 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{2}>0$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
u_{-}-u_{+}=F(p_{2};p_{\pm},\rho_{\pm})\label{eq:EquationForP2}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

will have a unique solution, in which case 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{2}$
\end_inset

 is
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u_{2}=\frac{u_{-}+u_{+}+f(p_{2};p_{+},\rho_{+})-f(p_{2};p_{-},\rho_{-})}{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{-}-u_{+}\le F(0;p_{\pm},\rho_{\pm})$
\end_inset

 or equivalently
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
u_{-}+\frac{2a_{-}}{\gamma-1}\le u_{+}-\frac{2a_{+}}{\gamma-1}\label{eq:VacuumCondition}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

then Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:EquationForP2"

\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{2}>0$
\end_inset

 will have no solution, which indicates something is wrong in the derivation
 of Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:EquationForP2"

\end_inset

.
 Physically, pressure is a measure of the intensity of gas molecules' thermal
 motion, so 
\begin_inset Formula $p=0$
\end_inset

 can only appears in a region of vacuum.
 Equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:VacuumCondition"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 is then called the 
\noun on
vacuum condition
\noun default

\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
condition!vacuum ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

, which means if the initial velocity gap 
\begin_inset Formula $(u_{-}-u_{+})$
\end_inset

 is sufficiently large, the flow field will be torn into two independent
 regions, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{1}\cup E_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{3}\cup C_{4}$
\end_inset

, being connected by a vacuumed region, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $C_{2}\cup E_{2}\cup C_{3}$
\end_inset

.
 It is reasonable to set 
\begin_inset Formula $\rho_{2}=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{2}=0$
\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset Formula $a_{2}=0$
\end_inset

) inside the vacuumed region.
 However, 
\begin_inset Formula $u_{2}$
\end_inset

 does not have to be 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{\pm}>p_{2}=0$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{3}$
\end_inset

 will both be rarefactions, inside which, states can be determined from
 the two Riemann invariants.
 For 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}$
\end_inset

, they are
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi_{1}=\frac{p}{\rho^{\gamma}}=\frac{p_{-}}{\rho_{-}^{\gamma}}\qquad\phi_{2}=u+\frac{2a}{\gamma-1}=u_{-}+\frac{2a_{-}}{\gamma-1}
\]

\end_inset

The speed of 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{1}$
\end_inset

's head is simply
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{1-}=u_{-}-a_{-}
\]

\end_inset

To find the speed of its tail, we shall use 
\begin_inset Formula $\phi_{2}$
\end_inset

, which leads to
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{1+}=u_{-}+\frac{2a_{-}}{\gamma-1}\impliedby\begin{cases}
v_{1+}=u_{1+}-a_{1+}\\
u_{-}+\frac{2a_{-}}{\gamma-1}=u_{1+}+\frac{2a_{1+}}{\gamma-1}\\
a_{1+}=a_{2}=0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

Similarly, the speed of 
\begin_inset Formula $E_{3}$
\end_inset

's head and tail are
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{3+}=u_{+}+a_{+}\qquad v_{3-}=u_{+}-\frac{2a_{+}}{\gamma-1}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Recall the vacuum condition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:VacuumCondition"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma>1$
\end_inset

, we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{1-}<v_{1+}<v_{3-}<v_{3+}
\]

